Two Canadian Banks Announce Hacks Over the Weekend
Two Canadian banks put out statements on Monday announcing separate cyber-incidents affecting their customers. The two are Simplii Financial, a subsidiary of CIBC, and the Bank of Montreal
https://www.bleepingcomputer.com/news/security/two-canadian-banks-announce-hacks-over-the-weekend/

Critical RCE Flaw Discovered in Blockchain-Based EOS Smart Contract System
Researchers have discovered a series of new vulnerabilities in EOS blockchain platform, one of which could allow remote hackers to take complete control over the node servers running the critical blockchain-based applications.
https://thehackernews.com/2018/05/eos-blockchain-smart-contract.html

Apple’s Macs Fall Prey to New Crypto Mining Attack
According to American Internet Security company Malwarebytes Inc., a recently discovered malicious XMRig-based crypto mining program is targeting Apple’s Mac computers by leeching their computing resources to mine Monero cryptocurrency
https://bitsonline.com/apple-mac-cryptojacking-attack-crypto/

